content: the quant firm offered me the job! it's official - i'm leading their AI trading team. also, had a coffee with my mentor; he's proud, but reminded me to keep learning. the journey's just beginning.

my first week leading the AI team was intense. we're optimizing the model for live trading. also, had a family dinner where my dad shared some wisdom about leadership. it's not just about coding, it's about people too.

just finished a 48-hour coding marathon. the AI model's now live in our trading platform. also, started exploring DeFi with my dev partner. the potential for AI and blockchain integration here is mind-blowing.
had an ethical debate with my team about AI in trading. it's not just about making money, it's about fairness too. also, took a break to enjoy some city life - the balance is key to staying grounded.

my AI model's first real-world test was a success. made a small profit with low risk. also, had a long chat with my mom about work-life balance. her perspective always brings me back to what really matters.

got invited to speak at another conference. this time on AI ethics in trading. also, my blockchain project is progressing; we're now testing our smart contracts in a simulated environment. every step forward feels like a win.
just had a breakthrough in our blockchain project. our smart contract now automates trade settlements seamlessly. also, had a date night; it's these moments that remind me why i'm working so hard.

spent the week refining our AI trading strategy for different market conditions. it's complex but rewarding. also, had a mentor session on leadership - it's not just about being the best, but bringing out the best in others.

got some feedback on our AI model from industry peers. they're impressed, but suggested some tweaks. back to the lab! also, just celebrated my 23rd birthday with family. grateful for their support, it keeps me grounded.
